  "intros": "<div class=\"tabs-container\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-800 mb-6 mt-6 text-center\">Lesson 6: Where to Place Your <script> Tag and Why</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-gray-600 text-lg mb-8 text-center px-4\">The location of your script tag matters more than you think. Let's learn the 'where' and 'why' for a faster, error-free website.</p>\n\n    <!-- Hidden radio buttons that control the state of the tabs -->\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab1\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\" checked>\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab2\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\">\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab3\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\">\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab4\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\">\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab5\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\">\n\n    <!-- Tab Header Buttons (styled labels) -->\n    <div class=\"tabs-header flex flex-row bg-gray-100 border-b border-gray-200 text-sm font-medium text-center text-gray-600 rounded-t-lg overflow-hidden\">\n        <label for=\"tab1\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label1\" title=\"The Assembly Line\">1</label>\n        <label for=\"tab2\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label2\" title=\"The Playwright's Script\">2</label>\n        <label for=\"tab3\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label3\" title=\"The Delivery Truck Race\">3</label>\n        <label for=\"tab4\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label4\" title=\"The Tool-belt\">4</label>\n        <label for=\"tab5\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label5\" title=\"The Gardner's Dilemma\">5</label>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Tab Content Panels -->\n    <div class=\"tab-content-container p-6 sm:p-8 border border-t-0 border-gray-200 rounded-b-lg\">\n        <!-- Tab 1 Content: The Assembly Line -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content1\" id=\"content1\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The Assembly Line</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">On a car assembly line, do you try to install the radio before the car's frame is even built?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#ffffff\" />\n                    <!-- Wrong Way -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(400, 450)\">\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#ef4444\" text-anchor=\"middle\">The Wrong Way (Script in Head)</text>\n                        <!-- Robot with radio -->\n                        <rect x=\"-50\" y=\"-50\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" fill=\"#78716c\"/>\n                        <rect x=\"-80\" y=\"-20\" width=\"30\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#a8a29e\"/>\n                        <rect x=\"-150\" y=\"-20\" width=\"50\" height=\"30\" fill=\"#facc15\"/>\n                        <!-- Error -->\n                        <path d=\"M-150,-20 l 50,50\" stroke=\"#ef4444\" stroke-width=\"6\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"28\" fill=\"#b91c1c\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\"Nowhere to put the radio!\"</text>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Right Way -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(1200, 450)\">\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#16a34a\" text-anchor=\"middle\">The Right Way (Script in Body)</text>\n                        <!-- Car Frame -->\n                        <path d=\"M-250,50 C-270,50 -280,20 -260,0 L -230,-50 C-220,-70 -150,-80 -100,-80 L50,-80\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#4b5563\" stroke-width=\"8\"/>\n                        <!-- Robot with radio -->\n                        <rect x=\"-50\" y=\"-50\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" fill=\"#78716c\"/>\n                        <rect x=\"-80\" y=\"-20\" width=\"30\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#a8a29e\"/>\n                        <rect x=\"-150\" y=\"-20\" width=\"50\" height=\"30\" fill=\"#facc15\"/>\n                        <path d=\"M-150,-5 L-100,-5\" stroke=\"#16a34a\" stroke-width=\"6\" stroke-dasharray=\"10 5\">\n                            <animate attributeName=\"stroke-dashoffset\" values=\"0;-15\" dur=\"1s\" repeatCount=\"indefinite\" />\n                        </path>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"28\" fill=\"#15803d\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\"Frame is ready, installing now!\"</text>\n                    </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    A browser builds a webpage from top to bottom, like a car on an assembly line. If you put your <span class=\"font-semibold text-gray-800\"><script></span> tag in the <span class=\"font-semibold text-gray-800\"><head></span>, you're telling the assembly line robot: \"Stop everything and install the radio now!\" The robot looks around and sees there's no car frame yetâ€”it has nothing to install the radio into. This causes an error.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    By placing the <span class=\"font-semibold text-gray-800\"><script></span> tag at the very end of the <span class=\"font-semibold text-gray-800\"><body></span>, you wait until the entire car frame (all your HTML elements) has been fully built. Then, you tell the robot to install the radio. Now it can easily find the dashboard and do its job without any errors.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">Build the car first, then add the electronics.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <!-- Tab 2 Content: The Playwright's Script -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content2\" id=\"content2\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The Playwright's Script</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">In a play, does the director give actors instructions before they've even walked on stage?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                 <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#ffffff\" />\n                    <!-- Script in Head (Wrong) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(400, 450)\">\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#ef4444\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Script in Head</text>\n                        <text x=\"-150\" y=\"-100\" font-family=\"serif\" font-size=\"32\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Director: \"Bob, move left!\"</text>\n                        <text x=\"150\" y=\"100\" font-family=\"serif\" font-size=\"32\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Bob: \"Who's Bob? I'm not on stage yet!\"</text>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Script in Body (Right) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(1200, 450)\">\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#16a34a\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Script in Body</text>\n                        <path d=\"M-200,200 L -150,-200 L 150,-200 L 200,200 Z\" fill=\"#a16207\"/>\n                        <circle cx=\"0\" cy=\"50\" r=\"30\" fill=\"#e0f2fe\"/><text x=\"0\" y=\"120\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"24\" fill=\"black\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Bob</text>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-100\" font-family=\"serif\" font-size=\"32\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Director: \"Bob, move left!\"</text>\n                    </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    Your HTML document is the stage, and your elements (`<h1>`, `<p>`, etc.) are the actors. Your JavaScript is the director, giving instructions. If the director (a `<script>` in the `<head>`) starts shouting commands before the play begins, the actors aren't on stage yet. The commands are directed at an empty stage, causing confusion and errors.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    The professional approach is to let all the actors get into position on stage first. By placing the `<script>` tag at the end of the `<body>`, you are ensuring that all the HTML elements have been created. Only then does the director step in and start giving commands. Now, when the director says \"find the element with the ID 'hero-title' and change its color,\" that actor is actually on stage and ready to receive the instruction.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">Let the actors take the stage before the director gives a command.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        \n        <!-- Tab 3 Content: The Delivery Truck Race -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content3\" id=\"content3\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The Delivery Truck Race</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">To build a house, which truck should arrive first: the one with the wood frame or the one with the furniture?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#ffffff\" />\n                    <!-- Script in Head (Slow) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(400, 450)\">\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#ef4444\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Script in Head (Blocks Rendering)</text>\n                         <!-- JS Truck -->\n                        <rect x=\"-150\" y=\"-50\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" fill=\"#3b82f6\" rx=\"10\"/> <text x=\"-120\" y=\"30\" font-size=\"32\" fill=\"white\">JS</text>\n                        <!-- HTML Truck Blocked -->\n                        <rect x=\"-50\" y=\"100\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" fill=\"#e5e7eb\" rx=\"10\"/> <text x=\"-20\" y=\"180\" font-size=\"32\" fill=\"black\">HTML</text>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Script in Body (Fast) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(1200, 450)\">\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#16a34a\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Script in Body (Doesn't Block)</text>\n                        <!-- HTML Truck -->\n                        <rect x=\"-250\" y=\"-50\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" fill=\"#d1d5db\" rx=\"10\"/> <text x=\"-220\" y=\"30\" font-size=\"32\" fill=\"black\">HTML</text>\n                        <!-- JS Truck arriving after -->\n                        <rect x=\"50\" y=\"100\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" fill=\"#bfdbfe\" rx=\"10\"/> <text x=\"80\" y=\"180\" font-size=\"32\" fill=\"black\">JS</text>\n                    </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    When a browser loads a page, it's like a construction site receiving deliveries. The HTML truck carries the essential structure (the wood frame). The CSS truck carries the paint. The JavaScript truck carries all the complex furniture and appliances.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    If you put the `<script>` tag in the `<head>`, the large JavaScript truck arrives first. The browser stops everything and waits for that entire truck to be unloaded before it will even accept the HTML truck. This means the user sees a <span class=\"font-semibold text-gray-800\">blank white screen</span> for a long time. This is called \"render-blocking.\" By putting the script at the end of the body, you let the HTML and CSS trucks arrive and build the visible structure of the house first. The user sees the page quickly, and the JavaScript furniture can be delivered and placed inside afterward.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">Let the user see the house first; deliver the furniture last.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        \n        <!-- Tab 4 Content: The Tool-belt -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content4\" id=\"content4\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The Tool-belt</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">A builder is putting up a wall. When should they grab the hammer from their tool-belt?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                 <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#ffffff\" />\n                    <!-- Script in Head -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(400, 450)\">\n                         <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#ef4444\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Script in Head</text>\n                         <!-- Hammer first -->\n                         <rect x=\"-50\" y=\"-100\" width=\"100\" height=\"50\" fill=\"#a8a29e\"/><rect x=\"-10\" y=\"-50\" width=\"20\" height=\"150\" fill=\"#a16207\"/>\n                         <text x=\"0\" y=\"200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"28\" fill=\"#b91c1c\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\"I have a hammer, but no nail!\"</text>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Script in Body -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(1200, 450)\">\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#16a34a\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Script in Body</text>\n                        <!-- Nail (HTML element) first -->\n                        <rect x=\"-5\" y=\"-100\" width=\"10\" height=\"100\" fill=\"#d1d5db\"/><path d=\"M-20 -100 L 20 -100 L 0 -120 Z\" fill=\"#d1d5db\"/>\n                        <!-- Hammer ready -->\n                        <rect x=\"50\" y=\"-50\" width=\"100\" height=\"50\" fill=\"#a8a29e\"/><rect x=\"90\" y=\"0\" width=\"20\" height=\"150\" fill=\"#a16207\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"28\" fill=\"#15803d\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\"I see the nail, now I'll grab my hammer.\"</text>\n                    </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    Your JavaScript code is a set of tools, like a hammer. Your HTML elements are the materials, like nails. A builder reads instructions (the browser reading the HTML file) from top to bottom.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    If the instruction to \"grab the hammer\" (the `<script>` tag) comes before the instruction \"here is a nail\" (the HTML element), the builder is stuck holding a tool with nothing to use it on. This causes an error. The correct sequence is to first be presented with the nail, <span class=\"font-semibold text-gray-800\">then</span> grab the hammer to act upon it. Placing the script at the end ensures all the \"nails\" (HTML elements) are laid out and ready before the \"hammer\" (JavaScript) is picked up to do its work.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">Present the material before you grab the tool.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        \n        <!-- Tab 5 Content: The Gardner's Dilemma -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content5\" id=\"content5\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The Gardner's Dilemma</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">To water a plant, do you pour the water before or after you've planted the seed?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#ffffff\" />\n                    <!-- Water first -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(400, 450)\">\n                         <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#ef4444\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Script in Head</text>\n                         <path d=\"M-50,0 C-50,-100 50,-100 50,0 L-50,0\" fill=\"#bfdbfe\"/>\n                         <text x=\"0\" y=\"-50\" font-size=\"24\">Water (JS)</text>\n                         <rect x=\"-100\" y=\"50\" width=\"200\" height=\"50\" fill=\"#a16207\"/>\n                         <text x=\"0\" y=\"200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"28\" fill=\"#b91c1c\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Watered empty ground.</text>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Seed first -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(1200, 450)\">\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#16a34a\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Script in Body</text>\n                        <rect x=\"-100\" y=\"50\" width=\"200\" height=\"50\" fill=\"#a16207\"/>\n                        <ellipse cx=\"0\" cy=\"50\" rx=\"20\" ry=\"15\" fill=\"#fde68a\"/>\n                         <text x=\"0\" y=\"20\" font-size=\"18\">Seed (HTML)</text>\n                        <path d=\"M0,-150 C0,-250 100,-250 100,-150 L0,-150\" fill=\"#bfdbfe\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"28\" fill=\"#15803d\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Watering the planted seed.</text>\n                    </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    Your HTML elements are like seeds that you need to plant in the ground. Your JavaScript is like the water that makes those seeds grow and come to life.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    Placing your `<script>` tag in the `<head>` is like pouring water on an empty patch of dirt. The seeds haven't been planted yet, so the water has nothing to act upon and is wasted. The browser tries to run your JavaScript, can't find the elements it's supposed to work on, and gives up. By putting the `<script>` tag at the end of the `<body>`, you are ensuring all the HTML \"seeds\" are planted in the document first. Then, the JavaScript \"water\" comes and can properly nourish each plant, making them grow as intended.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">Plant the seeds first, then add the water.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n<!--end-of-code-block-->",
